mkdir

~
Mkdir command in Linux allows the user to create directories.
The comand can create multiple directories at once as well as set the permissions for the directories.

The syntax for mkdir is:
  mkdir [options...] [directories ...]
  
For example, if you excute the following commnad:
  mkdir -p first/second/third

If the first and second directories do not exist the "-p" option will create these directories for us.
If we do note use the -p option and the first and second directory does not exits, we will get the following error message:
  
